<TITLE> 3 killed in the capital </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 8 (bdnews24.com)-- Three persons, including a child, were murdered in the capital on Saturday. An alleged criminal was killed in the city's Shyamali Saturday morning. Forty-year old Abdus Samad was shot, stabbed and slaughtered by criminals, said Riaz Ahmed, officer-in-charge of Sher-e-Bangla Nagar Police Station. There are at least seven cases including murder charges against Samad, he said. Meanwhile, 26-year old Yasmin Akhter and her four year-old daughter Erena Alam Talha were found dead at their home at Shanir Akhra in Jatrabari, on the outskirts of the capital. Their bodies were found tied up in bed. Kadamtali police sub-inspector Golam Mostafa said they had been strangled. Yasmin's husband Shah Alam lives outside Dhaka in his work place. Police are trying to ascertain the motive behind the murder. bdnews24.com/l
